<html>
  <head>
    <title>Twilio SDK beta 0.6.1</title>
  </head>
  <body>
    <ol>
      <li>Hit <em>connect</em>. You will see call controls appear if registration is successful.</li>
      <li>Rinse and repeat in a new tab/browser with a different name in the url: /index.php?name=participant2.</li>
      <li>In either browser, enter the <em>other</em> user's name and hit <em>call</em>.</li>
      <li>Add additional participants using the "add" button that appears when a conversation is live.</li>
    </ol>
    <div>
      <button id="connect">connect</button>
    </div>
    <div id="conversation">
      <div>
        <div id="remote-videos"></div>
      </div>
      <div>
        <video id="local-video"></video>
        <p class="video-label"><a href="#" id="preview">Preview Camera</a></p>
      </div>
      <div id="call-controls">
        <input id="name" type="text" placeholder="What is your name?"></input>
        <button id="submitName">Submit Name</button>
        <br />
        <input id="b-party" type="text" placeholder="who ya gonna call?"></input>
        <button id="call">call</button>
        <div id="n-party-controls">
          <input id="n-party" type="text" placeholder="let's make this a party"></input>
          <button id="add-party">add</button>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <script src="https://code.jquery.com/jquery-2.1.4.min.js"></script>
    <script src="//media.twiliocdn.com/sdk/conversations/v0.7/js/releases/0.7.0.b1-6af62af/twilio-conversations.js"></script>
    <script src="/js/socket.io.js"></script>
    <script src="/js/demo.js"></script>
    <script src="/js/demo2.js"></script>
    <script src="/js/video.js"></script>
  </body>
</html>
